# Sales Forecasting for a Global Food & Beverage Client

Forecasting monthly sales using 5 years of data from Snowflake. Built time-series models with Python (Prophet), created Power BI dashboards with DAX, and automated data pipelines for real-time reporting.

**Tools:** Python, SQL (Snowflake), Power BI, Excel

# Sales Forecasting Notebook

import pandas as pd
from prophet import Prophet
import snowflake.connector

# Connect to Snowflake
conn = snowflake.connector.connect(
    user='YOUR_USERNAME',
    password='YOUR_PASSWORD',
    account='YOUR_ACCOUNT'
)

query = """
SELECT sales_date, region, product_category, sales_amount
FROM sales_data_table
WHERE sales_date >= DATEADD(year, -5, CURRENT_DATE)
"""

df = pd.read_sql(query, conn)

# Prepare data
df['sales_date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['sales_date'])
monthly_sales = df.groupby('sales_date')['sales_amount'].sum().reset_index()

prophet_df = monthly_sales.rename(columns={'sales_date': 'ds', 'sales_amount': 'y'})

model = Prophet()
model.fit(prophet_df)

future = model.make_future_dataframe(periods=12, freq='M')
forecast = model.predict(future)

model.plot(forecast)
